1. e4 e5 { Let's look at one from black's perspective. } 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 { This is just about the most known position that I... know of... } 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Bc5 { Leaving the most common ideas. } 6. c3 b5 { Our moment to deviate arrives. } 7. Bb3 Ba7 { We can afford to be creative as the black player because our opponent has the same amount of exact information that we do in this position. Nada. Some ideas will overlap with the main moves, but memorization is out the window. } 8. d3 (8. Qe2) (8. Re1) (8. d4) (8. a4) *


