[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/DrHack"]
[UTCDate "2017.04.09"]
[UTCTime "01:09:24"]

1. e4 e6 2. Nc3 d5 3. Nf3 d4 4. Ne2 { Now that you are armed with the pre-knowledge that there is nothing wrong with your position (because you checked it with a computer). Go forth and play some original chess boldly. } 4... c5 5. c3 Nc6 { Databases can sometimes deceive you, be aware. My database in this position tells me that black wins most of the games. However, after a forced sequence: } 6. cxd4 cxd4 (6... Nf6 7. dxc5 Nxe4 8. Nc3 Nxc3 9. bxc3 Bxc5 10. d4 { The most challenging line to find as white. I still prefer white. }) 7. Qa4 { All of a sudden white wins most of the games in the database. This is because there are not enough games to give us a conclusion as to which side stands better in practice. This is a blank canvas. Good luck! } *


